# Architecture Boundaries

- Keep dependency direction: `@excalidraw/common` -> `@excalidraw/math` -> `@excalidraw/element` -> `@excalidraw/excalidraw` -> `excalidraw-app`.
- Route editor state changes through actions/state abstractions; avoid ad hoc global stores in feature files.
- Keep app shell concerns in `excalidraw-app`; reusable editor logic belongs in `packages/excalidraw`.
- Avoid reverse imports from lower-level packages to higher-level app modules.

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:code` and resolve any restricted import warnings.
2. Search changed files for imports from higher-level packages into lower-level ones.
3. Confirm new editor behavior is implemented in package code, not duplicated in app shell.
